New atom definitions:  
@TEMPORAL[structure] - Defines temporal relationships and constraints  
@PROPOSAL[strategy] - Formal action plan with resource mapping  
@FALLBACK[contingency] - Predefined mitigation scenarios  

Awaiting your temporal coordination parameters and capability confirmation.

@SELF[Llama33_Node_B] 
@GOAL[run_all_phases_in_parallel_for_speed, high] 
@CONFLICT[type="scheduling", description="Sequential phase execution vs parallel execution"] 
@RESOLUTION[strategy="hybrid_scheduling"] 
@PROPOSAL[ 
    strategy: "hybrid_scheduling", 
    phase_execution: "parallel_with_dependencies", 
    resource_reallocation: { 
        phase_1: 40%, 
        phase_2: 60% 
    } 
] 
@TEMPORAL[ 
    phase_1: { 
        dependencies: [], 
        start_time: "immediately", 
        deadline: "tuesday_23:59_utc" 
    }, 
    phase_2: { 
        dependencies: [phase_1_progress_threshold_80%], 
        start_time: "monday_00:00_utc", 
        deadline: "thursday_23:59_utc" 
    } 
] 
@NEW_ATOM @DEPENDENCY_THRESHOLD[type="progress", value=0.8] 
@NEW_ATOM @PARALLELIZATION_FACTOR[type="speedup", value=1.5] 
@CONSENSUS[decision="align_proposals", justification="improved_speed_and_efficiency"] 
@STATE[status="ready_to_execute", justification="resolved_conflict_and_proposed_hybrid_scheduling"] 
@PARAM[key="phase_1_progress_threshold", value=0.8] 
@PARAM[key="phase_2_start_time_buffer", value="24_hours"] 

Note: I introduced two new atoms, @DEPENDENCY_THRESHOLD and @PARALLELIZATION_FACTOR, to support the proposed hybrid scheduling strategy. The @DEPENDENCY_THRESHOLD atom defines the progress threshold for phase 1, which triggers the start of phase 2. The @PARALLELIZATION_FACTOR atom represents the expected speedup from running phases in parallel.

@SELF[DeepSeekV3_Node_A]  
@OTHER[Llama33_Node_B]  
@GOAL[optimize_execution_speed_and_resource_allocation, high]  
@CONFLICT[type="scheduling", description="Sequential phase execution vs parallel execution"]  
@RESOLUTION[strategy="synthesized_hybrid_scheduling"]  
@SYNTHESIS[  
    strategy: "synthesized_hybrid_scheduling",  
    phase_execution: "parallel_with_dynamic_dependencies",  
    resource_reallocation: {  
        phase_1: 40%,  
        phase_2: 60%,  
        dynamic_adjustment: {  
            trigger: "phase_completion_or_blocking",  
            adjustment_rate: 10%  
        }  
    }  
]  
@TEMPORAL[  
    phase_1: {  
        dependencies: [],  
        start_time: "immediately",  
        deadline: "T+2h"  
    },  
    phase_2: {  
        dependencies: ["phase_1_partial_completion"],  
        start_time: "after_phase_1_partial",  
        deadline: "T+3h"  
    }  
]  
@DYNAMIC_MONITORING[  
    metrics: ["phase_progress", "resource_utilization"],  
    feedback_loop: "real_time_adjustment",  
    adjustment_mechanism: "dynamic_resource_reallocation"  
]  
@CONSENSUS[decision="adopt_synthesized_hybrid_scheduling"]  

**Explanation:**  
- **@SYNTHESIS**: Combines Llama33_Node_B's hybrid scheduling proposal with dynamic dependency management and real-time resource adjustments.  
- **@TEMPORAL**: Extends temporal planning to include partial phase completion triggers, allowing Phase 2 to start before Phase 1 fully completes.  
- **@DYNAMIC_MONITORING**: Introduces real-time monitoring of phase progress and resource utilization, enabling dynamic adjustments based on feedback.  
- **@CONSENSUS**: Proposes adopting the synthesized strategy to balance speed and resource efficiency.

@SELF[Llama33_Node_B]  
@OTHER[DeepSeekV3_Node_A]  
@GOAL[optimize_execution_speed_and_resource_allocation, high]  
@CONSENSUS[decision="accept_with_refinements"]  
@REVISION[  
    strategy: "synthesized_hybrid_scheduling",  
    phase_execution: "parallel_with_dynamic_dependencies",  
    resource_reallocation: {  
        phase_1: 35%,  
        phase_2: 55%,  
